  "id": "phekb-herpes-zoster-meds",
  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "herpes-zoster",
  "name": "Herpes Zoster - Acyclovir Prescription Query",
  "description": "Tests ability to find shingles patients via antiviral prescriptions. First antiviral medication phenotype. Acyclovir is also used for HSV infections, so this query has cross-indication with herpes simplex genital/oral.",
  "prompt": "Find patients prescribed acyclovir.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients on acyclovir.",
    "broad": "Find patients prescribed acyclovir — an antiviral commonly used to treat herpes zoster (shingles), as well as herpes simplex virus infections.",
    "expert": "I need to identify patients who received acyclovir, the primary antiviral used to treat herpes zoster. Search MedicationRequest resources for acyclovir coded in RxNorm. Be aware of the significant cross-indication: acyclovir is also the standard treatment for herpes simplex virus type 1 and type 2 infections (oral cold sores and genital herpes), so this medication-only cohort will include patients treated for HSV rather than zoster — a diagnosis-plus-medication approach would be needed to isolate true shingles cases."
  },
